<H3> <TI>   Security Heightened in Mexico City </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0301140694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1300 
GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0301140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<FÊP=106> [From the "Panorama Newscast"] </F>
  [Excerpts] The civilian population in <LOCATION>San Cristobal</LOCATION> de las 
Casas, <LOCATION>Ocosingo</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Abasolo</PERSON>, <PERSON>Chanal del Carmen</PERSON>, and <ORGANIZATION>Las Margaritas</ORGANIZATION> 
face an uncertain situation, fearing new surprise attacks by the 
so-called <ORGANIZATION>Zapata National Liberation Army</ORGANIZATION>, which has declared a 
war on the <ORGANIZATION>Mexican Army</ORGANIZATION>. 
  There are scenes of destruction and death today. Members of 
the armed group are warning they will not remain entrenched. 
They intend to advance to the central part of the state and the 
country to demand the formation of what they call a free and 
democratic government. 
  The most recent offensive launched by the armed group 
resulted in the kidnapping of former <LOCATION>Chiapas</LOCATION> Governor General 
<PERSON>Absalon Castellanos</PERSON>. Approximately 40 heavily armed men arrived 
at his ranch in Margaritas municipality. There is still no clue 
as to the whereabouts of <PERSON>Absalon Castellanos</PERSON>. 
  Today, the <ORGANIZATION>Mexican Army</ORGANIZATION> controls the city of <LOCATION>San Cristobal</LOCATION> 
de 
las Casas, which was suddenly abandoned by the rebels who tried 
to storm the 31st Military Zone's general headquarters. 
However, the action was successfully repelled by the <ORGANIZATION>Mexican 
Army</ORGANIZATION>. 
  Clashes between the two sides in two days have left 57 dead. 
The <ORGANIZATION>Red Cross</ORGANIZATION> has decided not to go into areas of conflict 
given the lack of security for its humanitarian work. This 
follows attacks on two <ORGANIZATION>Red Cross</ORGANIZATION> ambulances in <LOCATION>San Cristobal de 
las Casas</LOCATION>, where a rescue team member was killed. The <ORGANIZATION>Red Cross</ORGANIZATION> 
is warning it lacks medicine and the necessary material to 
handle the emergency. [passage omitted] 
  The Judicial Police and the <ORGANIZATION>General Secretariat of 
Protection 
and Highways</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>Mexico City</LOCATION> have launched a special security 
operation which includes heightened security at government 
facilities, media installations, and embassies. This is being 
done as a precautionary measure to prevent any surprise takeover. 

</TEXT>

