<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<FÊP=106> [Bulletin No. 23 issued by the <ORGANIZATION>Mexican National Defense </F>
Secretariat</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>Mexico City</LOCATION> on 20 <DATE>January</DATE>; from the "24 Hours 
Newscast"] 
  [Text] As the process of normalization of the situation in 
highland, jungle, and border municipalities in <LOCATION>Chiapas State</LOCATION> 
progresses, most <ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION> troops remain confined to quarters near 
<LOCATION>San Cristobal</LOCATION> de las Casas, <LOCATION>Oxchuc</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Ocosingo</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Altamirano</PERSON>, and 
<LOCATION>Las Margaritas</LOCATION>, apart from <ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION> troops stationed at the military 
installations of <ORGANIZATION>Rancho Nuevo</ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION>Comitan</LOCATION>. This situation has 
permitted civilian authorities to carry out their normal 
activities and direct their efforts to provide humanitarian 
assistance to the population. 
  Soldiers continue to assist the civilian population by 
transporting and distributing supplies, blankets, and medicine 
to the affected towns. These actions are also being carried out 
freely by different social groups, the <ORGANIZATION>Red Cross</ORGANIZATION>, and 
nongovernment organizations. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION> will continue to participate in these humanitarian 
tasks and will assist civil institutions and organizations that 
require its assistance. 

</TEXT>

