<H3> <TI>   Rebels Maintaining Presence in at Least 5 Towns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0401021294 Paris AFP in Spanish 0108 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0401021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>San Cristobal</LOCATION> de las Casas, <LOCATION>Mexico</LOCATION>, 3 Jan (AFP) -- 
According to various sources, the <ORGANIZATION>Zapata National Liberation 
Army</ORGANIZATION> (<ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION>) is maintaining a guerrilla presence today in at 
least five towns of the southern State of <LOCATION>Chiapas</LOCATION>, leaving four 
mayors offices violently occupied in the past few days. 
  <PERSON>Rafael Gonzalez Lastra</PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION>Chiapas Government</ORGANIZATION> secretary 
general, has told a news conference that the <ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION> "aggressors" 
left the mayors offices in <LOCATION>Las Margaritas</LOCATION> and <PERSON>Chanal</PERSON> today and 
that <ORGANIZATION>Mexican Army</ORGANIZATION> troops are in the city of <LOCATION>Comitan</LOCATION>, south of 
<LOCATION>San Cristobal</LOCATION>, to guarantee peace. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION> forces violently seized the mayors offices in <LOCATION>San 
Cristobal</LOCATION> de las Casas, <LOCATION>Las Margaritas</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Chanal</PERSON>, <PERSON>Altamirano</PERSON>, and 
<LOCATION>Ocosingo</LOCATION> on 1 <DATE>January</DATE> in what constituted a violent guerrilla 
outbreak. 
  The guerrillas left <LOCATION>San Cristobal</LOCATION> on 2 <DATE>January</DATE> and moved 
toward <ORGANIZATION>Rancho Nuevo</ORGANIZATION>, where they have sustained several clashes 
with the troops stationed at the <ORGANIZATION>31st Military Zone Garrison</ORGANIZATION>. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION> presence continues in <LOCATION>Ocosingo</LOCATION>, where there have 
been clashes, and <PERSON>Altamirano</PERSON>, <LOCATION>Oxchuch</LOCATION>, Huiztan, and Cuxulja, 
which they occupied on <DATE>Sunday</DATE>. 
  Certain reports stated that a group of rebels has taken over 
<LOCATION>Guadalupe Tepeyac</LOCATION>, in <ORGANIZATION>Las Margaritas Municipality</ORGANIZATION>. 
  <PERSON>Gonzalez Lastra</PERSON> said he trusts that order will be 
reestablished in <LOCATION>Ocosingo</LOCATION> and <PERSON>Altamirano</PERSON> "within the next few 
hours." 
  Media reports, which authorities have not confirmed, state 
that the troops arrested 12 civilians in <LOCATION>Comitan</LOCATION>. Near the city 
an <ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION> unit kidnapped former <LOCATION>Chiapas</LOCATION> Governor <PERSON>Absalon 
Castellanos</PERSON> on <DATE>Sunday</DATE>. His whereabouts are unknown. 

</TEXT>

