<F P=102>  PA0401195294 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1857 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0401195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1857 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<FÊP=106> [From the "Good Afternoon From <LOCATION>Mexico</LOCATION>" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The situation in the <LOCATION>State of Chiapas</LOCATION> is as follows: 
  The Mexican <ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION> currently controls the city of <LOCATION>San 
Cristobal 
de Las Casas</LOCATION>. Clashes that took place <TIME>last night</TIME> in the 
municipality of <LOCATION>Ocosingo</LOCATION> resulted in 27 guerrillas and two 
soldiers dead. The city of Altamirano remains under <ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION> 
[<ORGANIZATION>Zapatista National Liberation Army</ORGANIZATION>] control while <ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION> aircraft 
continue to overfly the region. According to the latest 
reports, the community of (<PERSON>Wisan</PERSON>) remains under guerrillas 
control. In addition, the rebels withdrew from (Otchuc) without 
<ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION> intervention. 
  At least 2,000 additional soldiers arrived in <LOCATION>Tuxtla 
Gutierrez</LOCATION> which was already under control by the <ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION>. In <LOCATION>Las 
Margaritas</LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION> entered to retake the city, but it had 
already been abandoned by the guerrillas. The community of 
Chanal was already abandoned voluntarily by the <ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION>. 
  In concluding, the guerrillas announced they had mobilized 
in 
<PERSON>Venustiano Carranza</PERSON> and were present in other communities 
located along the <LOCATION>Chiapas</LOCATION> mountain range and the Guatemalan 
border. 

</TEXT>

