<H3> <TI>   EZLN Replies to Peace Commissioner's Proposal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0402035594 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0153 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0402035594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Indian Revolutionary Clandestine 
Committee-General Command [CCRI-CG] of the <ORGANIZATION>Zapatist National 
Liberation Army</ORGANIZATION> [<ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION>] has issued a new communique addressed to 
<PERSON>Samuel Ruiz Garcia</PERSON>, bishop of <LOCATION>San Cristobal</LOCATION> de las Casas and 
national mediation commissioner, and to <PERSON>Manuel Camacho Solis</PERSON>, 
commissioner for peace and reconciliation in <LOCATION>Chiapas</LOCATION>. The 
communique, dated 31 <DATE>January 1994</DATE>, has three points. 
  The first point reads: We received the letter from Peace 
Commissioner <PERSON>Camacho Solis</PERSON> dated 29 <DATE>January 1994</DATE> regarding the 
release of Division General <PERSON>Absalon Castellanos Dominguez</PERSON>. We 
have confirmed that the 38 prisoners mentioned were indeed 
released. Division General <PERSON>Castellanos Dominguez</PERSON> is in perfect 
health and knows he will be released soon. Division General 
<PERSON>Absalon Castellano</PERSON> will definitely be released. 
  The second point of the communique reads: We received the 
letter from Peace Commissioner <PERSON>Manuel Camacho Solis</PERSON> dated 29 
<DATE>January 1994</DATE> regarding the establishment of buffer or gray 
zones. We inform you that we fully agree with the entire 
proposal from the peace commissioner for peace and 
reconciliation in <LOCATION>Chiapas</LOCATION> in this respect. 
  The third point of the <ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION> communique reads: In saluting 
the clear intentions of the commissioner for peace and 
reconciliation in <LOCATION>Chiapas</LOCATION> to make advancements to alleviate the 
grave situation affecting the civilian population in the 
conflict areas, the CCRI-CG will order the immediate withdrawal 
of <ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION> troops from <LOCATION>Los Ejidos</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>San Miguel</LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION>Ococingo 
Municipality</ORGANIZATION>, and <LOCATION>Guadalupe Tepeyac</LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION>Las Margaritas 
Municipality</ORGANIZATION>. The <ORGANIZATION>EZLN</ORGANIZATION> troops will withdraw once the 
<ORGANIZATION>International Red Cross</ORGANIZATION> occupies these two buffer or gray zones 
and installs its camps for humanitarian aid. 
  The communique is signed by <PERSON>Subcommander Marcos</PERSON> and issued 
in 
the mountains of southeastern <LOCATION>Mexico</LOCATION>. 

</TEXT>

